Requirement Document: Basic Real-Time Chat App

1. Overview

This document outlines the requirements for a basic real-time chat application built using Node.js and Socket.IO. The application will provide a simple chat interface where users can join a single chat room and send messages that are broadcast to all other connected users.

2. Functional Requirements

Real-time Chat:
Users should be able to join the chat room upon visiting the application.
Users should be able to send text messages to the chat room.
Messages should be displayed in real-time for all connected users.
Messages should be timestamped to indicate when they were sent.
3. Non-Functional Requirements

Performance:

The application should handle a reasonable number of concurrent users without significant performance degradation.
Messages should be delivered to users in real-time with minimal latency.
Reliability:

The application should be highly available and reliable.
4. Technical Requirements

Server-Side:

Node.js and Express.js for building the server-side application.
Socket.IO for real-time communication.
Client-Side:

HTML, CSS, and JavaScript for building the user interface.
Socket.IO client library for real-time communication with the server.
5. Additional Considerations

User Experience:

The user interface should be simple and intuitive.
The chat experience should be smooth and seamless.